A composite literal whose `{` opens a line closes on its own line too. gofmt
never does this: go/printer decides the `}` break solely from whether the SOURCE
already put `}` on a later line (nodes.go:294), so `{\n\ta: 1}` stays welded shut.

Block-form braces and field-breaking are independent. breakWideLiterals treats a
literal as over budget when ANY line it spans overflows, not just its brace line.
The Import / Export item's `{` opens its own (short) line, but its fields are
packed onto one overflowing line, so that line is over budget and the fields
break one per line — the closing brace moves too, in block form. The Analytics
and Admin items are written fully inline, and at width 80 their brace lines (96
and 90 columns) are over budget, so breakWideLiterals breaks their fields the
same way.

-- input.gsx --
package ui

var appShellNavSections = []appShellNavSection{
	{
		label: "TOOLS",
		items: []appShellNavItem{
			{
				label: "Import / Export", page: ImportExportPage{}, pathMatch: "/import-export/", nonVendor: true, vendorVisible: func(u *db.UserInfo) bool { return u.HasGrantPrefix("", "import") }, },
			{label: "Analytics", page: DashboardLanding{}, pathMatch: "/dashboard/", nonVendor: true},
			{label: "Admin", page: AdminDashboardPage{}, pathMatch: "/admin/", adminOnly: true},
		},
	},
}
-- fmt.golden --
package ui

var appShellNavSections = []appShellNavSection{
	{
		label: "TOOLS",
		items: []appShellNavItem{
			{
				label:         "Import / Export",
				page:          ImportExportPage{},
				pathMatch:     "/import-export/",
				nonVendor:     true,
				vendorVisible: func(u *db.UserInfo) bool { return u.HasGrantPrefix("", "import") },
			},
			{
				label:     "Analytics",
				page:      DashboardLanding{},
				pathMatch: "/dashboard/",
				nonVendor: true,
			},
			{
				label:     "Admin",
				page:      AdminDashboardPage{},
				pathMatch: "/admin/",
				adminOnly: true,
			},
		},
	},
}
